-- Escaped 1973 Slayer of N.J. Trooper Added to FBI Terrorist List
-- B y   E r i k   L a r s o n
-- 2013-05-02T15:16:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-02/escaped-1973-slayer-of-n-j-trooper-added-to-fbi-terrorist-list.html
Joanne Chesimard, the Black Liberation
Army militant who fled prison for Cuba after being convicted of
killing a New Jersey state trooper in 1973, was added to the FBI
most-wanted terrorist list, and a reward for her capture was
doubled to $2 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Larson in  New York  at 
 elarson4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
